The President, along with his wife Jill, visited the Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point in North Carolina. He expressed gratitude to the Marines and sailors of the 2nd Marine Expeditionary Force for their service and sacrifices. The President acknowledged the importance of equipping and caring for those in harm's way and their families. He praised the military as the backbone and spine of the country, highlighting their dedication and the sacrifices made by their loved ones. The President also emphasized that the United States has the greatest fighting force in the world. He thanked the spouses for their support and mentioned the empty chairs at home during deployments. The President concluded by wishing the military a happy Thanksgiving and Christmas and thanked them once again for their service.